tant dimension of the linguistic landscape everywhere, as well as the reflection of the process of globalisation, visible through the use of English. The study of the linguistic landscape is applied here as a means to increase our understanding of multilingualism and future directions are outlined.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLinguistic change. 0aLinguistic minorities. 0aMultilingualism. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAmara, Muhammad Hasan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBackhaus, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCenoz, Jasone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorter, Durk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorter, Durk, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHecht, Nira Trumper-, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuebner, Thom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRafael, Eliezer Ben-, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShohamy, Elana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102473808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106067130 cprintz978185359916340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359917040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853599170423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853599170/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000